HEADWORD: Wind-rode
<hw>Wind"-rode`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>Caused to ride or drive by the wind in opposition to the course of
the tide; -- said of a vessel lying at anchor, with wind and tide
opposed to each other.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

